Basically what Hollywood does all the time lately _"If it's bigger, then it's gotta be better"_ motto. Same what happened with the new Star Wars... bigger "death star", bigger scale of destruction. And of course it's gonna be patched with a bunch of CGI, since nowadays they're incapable of making a decent horror by using a skin-crawling story and talent.  The Ring was always about something personal, like a loss intertwined with isolation and later on dread, not planes crashing from the sky. In Ring 4 we'll probably see her on that big screen in New York square or in McDonalds commercial, followed by people dying all over the place.  Thank you, but I'm gonna avoid this one.

text: I'll just be written off as a "hater" who needs to let the past go or whatever, but I also remember seeing the first sequel in the theater and almost walking out and demanding a refund before falling sleep at the 2/3 point. No exaggeration. The first American Ring film, despite some dumb moments, is a horror classic. A horror classic immediately followed up with a sequel that understood nothing about why the first film worked as well as it did, even with a kind of cheesy plot. This franchise died with the 2nd film. In fact it shouldn't have been a remake franchise at all. The first film was perfectly bookended. A good mystery from beginning to end. So no, I'm not surprised this looks like it'll be just as bad as the 2nd film. This is what happens when you wrap up your story so well the first time around. text: The music and camera-work in this movie makes the movie feel like an action or suspense movie. This movie felt like they're rushing straight to the point with lots of suspenseful/action music. Camera work is pretty garbage and it also feels like the movie is an action movie. Everything is 2 fast in this movie.  Horror movies are meant to move really slow with slow camera work and slow music.  This movie does not feel like a horror movie, due to poor camera work and poor music. Feels more like a suspense television show.  Horror movies are suppose to go really slow with slow camera movement (so they paint the picture of a horror movie).  Bad music, bad camera work, good actors, movie feels like a action/suspense movie . They rushed through this movie and ruined it.  5 out of 10.  Don't bother.

text: Everything wrong with 'Rings' (SPOILERS) not that you should care...    First let me just say this movie is a perfect example of what happens in Hollywood where too many people have their hands on something and have slices of creative control. You end up with this mess of a film that doesn't know what it wants to be, does it wanna be a sequal? A reimagining? An origin story? A piece of shit?    They invent this 'tail' thing for the movie (where you make a copy of the tape and tell someone to watch it and it lifts your curse) anyway they do basically nothing with it, except at the start. I can think of a million interesting things they could have done with that through side stories or something.    They barely show an entire run through of the ring tape without cuts to character reactions, part of what made the original movies enjoyable was when you get to watch the tape in its infinite weirdness, as the character watches it, they don't seem to want to do that I'm this film, instead they want you to see how the characters face looks as it plays...    Just as big bang theory dude is dying in the car and the girl grabs his hand, it builds it up like his character is gonna have some important last words that will lead to something, but instead nothing comes from the scene.  Bar a final destination style electrical post falling onto the car? (am I watching ring or final destination, wtf)    All jump scares feel wrongly timed, and are also not scary at all (one jump scare is a little millipede crawling out of a fucking hole in a wall...)    There's no character development, after the introduction of characters, they don't continue to develop, the writers and the director basically say "here's your little life, now you can't grow for the rest of the film" not only that but, there's no comrodery between characters, not only can nobody in the movie act, but they can't seem to build relationships convincingly either. I feel like these people just met each other an hour ago...    The fact that the main girl has brail scarred into her hand, and just as the guy leaves a message to tell her it's brail.. She meets a blind guy, lmao, it's laughable.    I could list a million more things but I cba, this film is junk I won't waste no more time on it. The crew with their names attached to it, should feel utterly embarrassed.

text: Okay, I just watched the movie last night. It wasn't as complete garbage as I was expecting, but yes, a ton of these scenes aren't in the movie or play out differently. Maybe I am forgetting some things, but here is my list of what isn't in the movie (trying to keep it spoiler-free): 0:33 The house with one light on. This could be a quick transition shot, but I don't remember that. 0:36 Was anyone sending Julia emails telling her to watch the video? That isn't how it plays out in the movie at all, so I would think no. 0:47 The webcam with water coming out of it. I am pretty sure this didn't happen. 0:59 Julia never says "That's when she is coming for me" standing around the fire. 1:00 No one has a ring on their back. 1:36 The arms don't wrap around her like that. 1:41 And the HUGE one that really made people realize there was a ton of BS in this trailer, the fact that no one's hands ever fuse together like that. 1:43 No one is standing in the building when everything starts flying up into the air. 1:48 The "mom" scene doesn't happen. In fact, I don't think there is any reference to Julia's mom at all. 1:59 The blind man never said "You've opened up a door, and now no one is safe". Why did they do this? I suspect it is because this movie's release was delayed multiple times it is possible there are several very different cuts of it.
